<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
MORTGAGES, MORTGAGE BANKERS, MORTGAGE-BACKED SECURITIES (MOR)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report.
                                                                                                       

                         CORPORATE
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Security Pacific Corp. -- $100 million of notes due Sept.
15, 1993, priced at par to float quarterly at 25 basis points
above the London interbank offered rate. The initial coupon
rate will be set Friday. The noncallable notes will pay
interest quarterly, with the first interest payment being
made Dec. 19. Rated single-A-1 by Moody's Investors Service
Inc. and double-A-minus by Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., the issue
will be sold through underwriters led by First Boston Corp.
                                                                                                       

                         MORTGAGES
                                                                                                       

   Capstead Securities -- $100 million of collateralized
mortgage obligations offered in six classes by Morgan Stanley
&amp; Co. The securities, which carry coupon rates of 9.60% to
9.90%, were priced Thursday. The offering, through Capstead
1990-2, is backed by 30-year whole loans with a weighted
average coupon rate of 10.782% and weighted average remaining
term to maturity of 29.83 years. Yield spreads and other
details weren't available.
                                                                                                       

                         EUROBONDS
                                                                                                       

   Nationwide Anglia Building Society (U.K.) -- #75 million
of fungible 13 5/8% Eurobonds due March 8, 1994, priced at
102.10 via Samuel Montagu &amp; Co. Yield, less full fees, is 106
basis points over comparable gilt, or British government
bond. Fees 1 5/8.
   Uniden Corp. (Japan) -- $120 million of Eurobonds due
Sept. 20, 1994, with equity-purchase warrants, indicating a 5
1/8% coupon at par, via Nomura International Ltd. Guaranteed
by Sanwa Bank Ltd. Each $5,000 bond carries one warrant,
exercisable from Oct. 4, 1990, through Sept. 13, 1994, to buy
shares at an expected 2 1/2% premium over the closing price
when terms are fixed Tuesday. Fees 2 1/4.
   Starts Corp. (Japan) -- 63 million Swiss francs of
privately placed convertible notes due Dec. 31, 1994, with a
fixed 4 3/4% coupon at par via Nomura Bank Switzerland. Put
option Dec. 31, 1992, at 108.50 to yield 8.25%. Each 50,000
Swiss franc note convertible from Oct. 18, 1990, to Dec. 16,
1994. Final conversion terms to be fixed Monday. Fees 1.38.
</TEXT>
