<LP>
   LEXINGTON, Mass. -- Raytheon Co. said it expects to report
a $17.5 million one-time charge against third-quarter
earnings related to the closure of a unit's Topton, Pa.,
manufacturing plant.
   Raytheon, an electronics, aircraft and missile concern,
had net income of $137.4 million, or $2.08 a share, on sales
of $2.2 billion for the 1989 third quarter.
</LP>
