   Philippines Logs a Trade Surplus
</HL>
<DATE>
09/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   MANILA, the Philippines -- The Philippines' trade surplus
with the U.S. for the first half narrowed 16% to $271.2
million from a $324.1 million surplus a year earlier, the
National Statistics Office said.
   Exports to the U.S. rose 17% in the half, and imports
gained at a much faster rate of 29%, the agency said.
</LP>
