that could prove more powerful than a line IBM is expected to
announce today.
                                                                                                       

   Adobe Systems won a partial victory in its battle with
Apple Computer and Microsoft to retain its hold on the market
for desktop publishing.
   ---
   The "payola" case against record promoter Joseph Isgro and
two others was dismissed by a federal judge, who harshly
criticized prosecutors for withholding evidence.
   ---
   CBS Records' Walter Yetnikoff is stepping down immediately
as chief executive of Sony's unit, accelerating his previous
plans to leave.
   ---
   Subaru of America's Harvey Lamm resigned as chairman and
chief executive. Two executives of Fuji Heavy Industries,
Subaru's new parent, succeed Lamm.
   ---
   Europe's semiconductor program is falling victim to an
industry shake out. N.V. Philips is withdrawing from a key
project in the effort.
   ---
   Private placements of securities plunged by one-third to
$55.3 billion in the first half of this year.
