</SO>
<CO>
   A.PCM
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
COAL PRODUCERS (COA)
PRECIOUS METALS, STONES, GOLD, SILVER (PCS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Pancontinental Mining Ltd. of Australia reported that for
the year ended June 30, after-tax operating profit rose 9% to
27.3 million Australian dollars (US$22.2 million) from A$25.1
million a year earlier.
   Per-share earnings rose to 16.5 Australian cents from 15.2
cents. The dividend was kept at 3.5 cents a share.
</LP>
