<HL>
   Business Brief -- Campeau Corp.:
   Retail Units' Losses in July
   Were Less Than Expected
</HL>
<DATE>
09/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   CMAFC
</CO>
<IN>
BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)
BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Campeau Corp.'s retail units, Federated Department Stores
Inc. and Allied Stores Corp., reported net losses of $50
million in July, "substantially less than expected," the
companies said.
   In documents filed with U.S. Bankruptcy Court in
Cincinnati, Federated said it had a net loss of $31.7 million
for the four weeks ended Aug. 4. For the previous period, the
five weeks ended July 7, Federated reported net losses of
$30.6 million. Meanwhile, Allied posted a net loss of $18.3
million in July compared with $18.6 in the previous period.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company noted that the net losses included non-cash
interest and interest on the company's pre-petition debt,
which account for about $35.1 million of the units' $42.6
million interest expense. The results also include a $2.5
million one-time charge due to an accounting change.
   Analysts noted that seasonal factors and the absence of
year-earlier comparisons make it difficult to assess
Federated and Allied's progress since seeking Chapter 11
bankruptcy protection on Jan. 15.
   Janet Mangano, an analyst at Jesup, Josephthal &amp; Co. in
New York, noted that the latest results were "rather
encouraging."
   Federated's sales for the four weeks were $263.5 million,
while Allied's sales were $150.1 million.
   In the combined June-July period, Federated had $3.5
million in cash flow while Allied had $1.94 million.
</TEXT>
