newspaper since 1988. A successor hasn't been named.
   Donald F. Wright, 56, senior vice president, assumed added
responsibility for various financial and administrative
functions of Times Mirror, including budget and planning. He
relinquishes responsibility to Mr. Schlosberg for four
newspapers. He continues to oversee the company's broadcast
and cable television groups.
