<HL>
   Who's News:
   PLM International's
   Megeath Quits Board
</HL>
<DATE>
09/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B12
</SO>
<CO>
   PLM WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
INDUSTRIAL &amp; COMMERCIAL SERVICES, LEASING, CLEANING (ICS)
</IN>
<LP>
   SAN FRANCISCO -- S.A. Megeath III announced his
resignation from the board of PLM International Inc. after
being stripped of the chairmanship and all other positions
except his directorship.
   In tendering his resignation, Mr. Megeath, 44 years old,
cited "intense" disagreement with the board over the
company's operations, policies and practices. In an
interview, he also complained that he had been kept in the
dark on company activity by management. But he declined to
elaborate on the substance of the dispute. PLM officials
didn't return phone calls.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   PLM announced that its board had elected J. Alec Merriam
as the new chairman. Mr. Merriam is an investor and formerly
executive vice president of Crowley Maritime Corp. Robert
Tidball, PLM's chief executive officer and president, whom
Mr. Megeath singled out for criticism, wasn't immediately
available for comment.
   PLM is a transportation equipment leasing company.
</TEXT>
